// const applayout most outer part of the project and what it contain all the other thingd

// what is javascript component at the end it is a function that return a piece of jsx code 



// > props are the properties that can be passed to a component
// > they are used to pass data and functionality from parent to child component
// > in this case, Resturantcard component is receiving restaurant name, logo, rating, and distance as props
// > react is wrapping inside the object and passing the props to the component
// > this is how we pass data and functionality between components
//   and to pass this we use {props.propertyName} in the child component
// > here, props.propertyName is the name of the property we want to access in the child component
  
// ** example
//   <Resturantcard name="Meghna Foods" logo="https://th.bing.com/th/id/OIP.wn6359RI5W7SXB4Zf8nZIQHaFj?pid=ImgDetMain" rating="4.4 stars" distance="38 minutes"/>
//   in the above example, Resturantcard component is receiving 3 properties name, logo, rating, and distance



//   my code is looking like this when we do not use array and take object from real code 
  import React from "react";
import ReactDOM from "react-dom/client";

